---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="SocialProof vs Yelp — Own Your Reviews on Your Own Site | SocialProof" description="Yelp reviews live on Yelp's platform. With SocialProof, collect testimonials and display them on YOUR website — where you control the narrative. Free to start." canonical="https://socialproof.dev/vs/yelp">
<style>
    body { font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif; margin: 0; background: #fff; color: #111; }
    .hero { text-align: center; padding: 4rem 2rem 2rem; max-width: 760px; margin: 0 auto; }
    .vs-badge { display: inline-block; background: #f0f0f0; color: #555; font-size: 0.8rem; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: .06em; text-transform: uppercase; padding: .35rem .75rem; border-radius: 99px; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
    .hero h1 { font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem); font-weight: 800; line-height: 1.15; margin: 0 0 1rem; }
    .hero h1 span { color: #4f46e5; }
    .hero p { font-size: 1.15rem; color: #444; max-width: 560px; margin: 0 auto 2rem; }
    .hero-cta { display: inline-block; background: #4f46e5; color: #fff; padding: .85rem 2rem; border-radius: 8px; font-weight: 700; text-decoration: none; font-size: 1rem; }
    section { max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 3rem 2rem; }
    h2 { font-size: 1.6rem; font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
    .compare-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 2rem 0; }
    .compare-table th { padding: .75rem 1rem; text-align: left; font-size: 0.85rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: .05em; color: #888; border-bottom: 2px solid #eee; }
    .compare-table th:nth-child(2) { color: #4f46e5; }
    .compare-table td { padding: .85rem 1rem; border-bottom: 1px solid #f0f0f0; font-size: 0.97rem; vertical-align: top; }
    .compare-table tr:last-child td { border-bottom: none; }
    .compare-table td:first-child { color: #555; font-weight: 500; }
    .yes { color: #16a34a; font-weight: 600; }
    .no { color: #dc2626; font-weight: 600; }
    .partial { color: #d97706; font-weight: 600; }
    .callout { background: #fef2f2; border: 1px solid #fecaca; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem 2rem; margin: 2rem 0; }
    .savings-box { background: #fffbeb; border: 1px solid #fcd34d; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem 2rem; margin: 2rem 0; }
    .bottom-cta { text-align: center; background: #4f46e5; color: #fff; border-radius: 16px; padding: 3.5rem 2rem; margin: 3rem 0; }
    .bottom-cta h2 { color: #fff; margin-bottom: .75rem; }
    .bottom-cta p { color: rgba(255,255,255,.8); margin-bottom: 2rem; font-size: 1.05rem; }
    .bottom-cta a { display: inline-block; background: #fff; color: #4f46e5; padding: .9rem 2.25rem; border-radius: 8px; font-weight: 700; text-decoration: none; font-size: 1rem; }
</style>
<main>
  <div class="hero">
    <span class="vs-badge">Comparison</span>
    <h1>SocialProof vs <span>Yelp</span></h1>
    <p>Yelp reviews live on Yelp's site — not yours. With SocialProof, collect testimonials from your best clients and display them directly on your website, where the buying decision happens.</p>
    <a href="https://app.socialproof.dev/signup" class="hero-cta">Try SocialProof Free →</a>
  </div>

  <section>
    <div class="callout">
      <strong>The fundamental problem with Yelp:</strong> Every review you earn sends traffic to Yelp, not your website. Visitors see your competitors' ads right next to your listing. You don't own the experience.
    </div>

    <h2>What's actually different</h2>
    <table class="compare-table">
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Feature</th><th>SocialProof</th><th>Yelp</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Reviews live on</td><td class="yes">Your website</td><td class="no">Yelp's website</td></tr>
        <tr><td>You control display</td><td class="yes">✓ Full control</td><td class="no">Yelp controls layout &amp; ads</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Competitor ads shown</td><td class="yes">✗ Never</td><td class="no">✓ Yes — on your listing</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Ask clients directly</td><td class="yes">✓ Yes — share a link</td><td class="no">Against Yelp's TOS</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Approve before display</td><td class="yes">✓ Yes</td><td class="no">No — public immediately</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Embed on your site</td><td class="yes">✓ Yes — copy/paste</td><td class="partial">Badge only (links to Yelp)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Business model</td><td class="yes">You're the customer</td><td class="no">Advertisers are the customer</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Review removal</td><td class="yes">✓ You control</td><td class="no">Yelp decides</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Free plan available</td><td class="yes">✓ Yes — 1 widget free</td><td class="partial">Free listing (ads shown)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Cost to remove competitor ads</td><td class="yes">N/A — no ads ever</td><td class="no">$300+/month Yelp Ads</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h2>The Yelp business model conflict</h2>
    <p>Yelp's revenue comes from advertising. That means competitors can pay to show their ads on your business page. When a prospect reads your glowing reviews on Yelp and sees "Also consider these nearby businesses," you've lost control of the sales conversation.</p>
    <p style="margin-top:1rem;">Yelp also restricts you from directly asking customers to leave reviews — doing so can get reviews filtered or your listing penalized. You're building on someone else's platform with their rules, their ads, and their incentives.</p>

    <h2>Use both — strategically</h2>
    <p>Yelp still matters for local SEO and discovery. You don't need to abandon it. But <strong>your website</strong> is where closing happens — and that's where your social proof needs to be strongest.</p>
    <p style="margin-top:1rem;">Use SocialProof to collect testimonials from your happiest clients (the ones you'd want on Yelp anyway) and display them directly on your services page, homepage, or booking page. Drive Yelp traffic to your site. Convert with testimonials you control.</p>

    <div class="savings-box">
      <h3>💡 The ownership argument</h3>
      <p>Every testimonial you collect with SocialProof is yours — export it anytime, use it in email marketing, on print materials, in proposals. Reviews on Yelp belong to Yelp's platform. Own your social proof.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bottom-cta">
      <h2>Your testimonials, on your website</h2>
      <p>Collect and display client testimonials where you control the experience. Free forever for 1 widget.</p>
      <a href="https://app.socialproof.dev/signup">Start Free — No Credit Card →</a>
    </div>

    <p style="font-size:0.9rem;color:#888;margin-top:2rem;">Also compare: <a href="/vs/google-reviews">vs Google Reviews</a> · <a href="/vs/trustpilot">vs Trustpilot</a> · <a href="/vs/birdeye">vs Birdeye</a> · <a href="/vs/nicejob">vs NiceJob</a> · <a href="/vs/podium">vs Podium</a></p>
  </section>
</main>
</Base>
